OL,3,CShould cruise ship passengers be
OL,4,Ccharged a tourist tax to visit
OL,5,CScotland?
OL,7,FCruise tourism is on the rise in
OL,8,FScotland, particularly across the
OL,9,Fislands, where it has become a major
OL,10,Findustry, creating jobs and providing
OL,11,Fa boost to the economies of the small
OL,12,Fcommunities.
OL,14,FLast year, there were around 1,000
OL,15,Fcruise visits into Scottish ports,
OL,16,Fwhich brought 1.2 million passengers -
OL,17,Fan increase of almost 400,000 compared
OL,18,Fto five years ago.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
