OL,3,CShould cruise ship passengers be
OL,4,Ccharged a tourist tax to visit
OL,5,CScotland?
OL,7,FThe sector is particularly important
OL,8,Fin islands like Shetland, where cruise
OL,9,Fpassengers now account for around 20%
OL,10,Fof all visitors.
OL,12,FLocals in its main town and port of
OL,13,FLerwick are mixed about whether a tax
OL,14,Fwould be a good thing in order to pay
OL,15,Ffor infrastructure investment, as many
OL,16,Fare worried it could hinder the
OL,17,Fcrucial business opportunities the
OL,18,Fcruises provide.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
