OL,3,CShould cruise ship passengers be
OL,4,Ccharged a tourist tax to visit
OL,5,CScotland?
OL,7,FRoss Manson is the co-owner of No 88
OL,8,FKitchen and Bar in the town, and he
OL,9,Fhas adapted his business's opening
OL,10,Fhours to tie in with the cruise ship
OL,11,Ftimetables and even the nationalities
OL,12,Fof its passengers.
OL,14,F"Each of the different cruises brings
OL,15,Fdifferent people, different numbers
OL,16,Fand different spend, so over the time
OL,17,Fthat we've been open, we have tried to
OL,18,Flearn from the previous year and then
OL,19,Fput that into action this year to be
OL,20,Fable to adapt," he told ITV News.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/18
